FBIS3-57428 "drsov017_b_94018" FBIS-SOV-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Aide Opposes Election of Local Heads MK2501150594 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 25 Jan 94 p 2 MK2501150594 Moscow SEGODNYA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "`Elections of Local Administration Heads Undesirable at This Stage'"] [Text] Nikolay Medvedev, chief of the Russian Federation president's administration for work with the territories, said that during a transition period of two years it is essential to ensure the stability, unity, and governability of the executive authority system both in the center and in the field. Given this, he expressed his opinion that holding elections of local administration chiefs would be "undesirable," because it is on the local chiefs that "Russia's stability and the stability of the very system of state authority" will depend.
